      "QID": "3",
      "question": "Which other COVID-19 control requirements will you change based on vaccines",
       "multiple": true,
      "description": "One of the advantages of vaccination is that it allows people to more safely return to regular activities. By changing policies for the vaccinated, you may encourage more people to choose vaccination",
      "resources": [],
      "answers": [
        {
          "AID": "3a",
          "prettyAID": "a",
          "answer": "Testing",
          "description": "The CDC does not recommend asymptomatic screening for fully vaccinated individuals.",
          "resources": [],
          "nextQID": "3a-i"
        },
        {
          "AID": "3b",
          "prettyAID": "b",
          "answer": "Quarantine",
          "description": "The CDC says that asymptomatic fully vaccinated people should not be required to quarantine after close exposure.",
          "resources": [],
          "nextQID": "3b-i"
        },
        {
          "AID": "3c",
          "prettyAID": "c",
          "answer": "Distancing",
          "description": "The CDC guidelines state that fully vaccinated people can gather without physical distancing. However, this applies only to fully vaccinated people; un-vaccinated or partially vaccinated people should still limit their close contact with other un-vaccinated or partially vaccinated people.",
          "resources": [],
          "nextQID": "3c-i"
        },
        {
          "AID": "3d",
          "prettyAID": "d",
          "answer": "Masks",
          "description": "The CDC has said that fully vaccinated people do not need to wear masks, with the exception of in healthcare facilities, on public transit, and where required by local regulations. However, they recommend that K-12 schools maintain their mask policies at present.",
          "resources": [],
          "nextQID": "3d-i"
        },
        {
          "AID": "3e",
          "prettyAID": "e",
          "answer": "Activities",
          "description": "While vaccine requirements for school may be difficult to enforce, vaccine and/or testing requirements for extracurricular activities can be helpful to encourage uptake. This is especially important, as these activities have been associated with higher risk of infection spread.",
          "resources": [],
          "nextQID": "3e-i"
        }
      ]
    },
